00:42:28,920 --> 00:42:31,639
it's that you can't trust the people in power.

1077
00:42:32,679 --> 00:42:37,679
And what if they assassinate Kavlaranan I.

1078
00:42:38,799 --> 00:42:40,440
I mean, I hope not.

1079
00:42:40,440 --> 00:42:41,879
Kavlaranan how long would it take you

1080
00:42:41,880 --> 00:42:45,519
to transcribe one of these books into your own?

1081
00:42:48,119 --> 00:42:51,480
You know what, I could get one done tonight for sure.

1082
00:42:51,480 --> 00:42:52,840
Would that hold up though?

1083
00:42:53,960 --> 00:42:56,760
Oh no, I would take the originals with me

1084
00:42:56,760 --> 00:43:01,200
and I'd leave you the copy, just so there was something.

1085
00:43:01,200 --> 00:43:03,280
They're gonna need to see these ones.

1086
00:43:03,280 --> 00:43:05,640
No point in having a copy if you've got the original

1087
00:43:05,640 --> 00:43:07,680
as you're taking it where it needs to go.

1088
00:43:07,680 --> 00:43:10,559
What if they're taking money from like Kinney and stuff?

1089
00:43:12,599 --> 00:43:14,160
You guys know Kinney, right?

1090
00:43:14,160 --> 00:43:16,280
From what I saw, it looks like they're taking money

1091
00:43:16,280 --> 00:43:17,119
from everyone.

1092
00:43:17,119 --> 00:43:21,840
Yeah, but like, what if we were able to look at it all

1093
00:43:21,840 --> 00:43:26,840
and then, you know, and then we know some stuff

1094
00:43:28,519 --> 00:43:31,640
because it's important to know stuff.

1095
00:43:31,640 --> 00:43:34,480
You know when you know something about somebody

1096
00:43:34,480 --> 00:43:38,200
and they don't want anybody else to know that thing,

1097
00:43:38,200 --> 00:43:39,039
right?

1098
00:43:39,039 --> 00:43:42,800
So they might be more likely to do the thing

1099
00:43:42,800 --> 00:43:45,679
that you want them to do or something like that

1100
00:43:45,679 --> 00:43:48,880
that I heard other people say that I have never done.

1101
00:43:48,880 --> 00:43:51,360
I feel like guys, I don't know the whole plan.

1102
00:43:52,519 --> 00:43:54,800
Well, cause we're just making it up as we go.

1103
00:43:54,800 --> 00:43:55,639
Yeah.

1104
00:43:55,639 --> 00:43:56,480
What?

1105
00:43:56,480 --> 00:43:59,440
I mean, now we maybe have proof of the corruption.

1106
00:43:59,440 --> 00:44:00,719
Perfect.

1107
00:44:00,719 --> 00:44:03,840
Now we get proof of the corruption to the authorities.

1108
00:44:03,840 --> 00:44:06,400
What if they take it and they don't do anything?

1109
00:44:06,400 --> 00:44:08,800
Then we just gave them all of our stuff.

1110
00:44:08,800 --> 00:44:10,440
They'll do something.

1111
00:44:10,440 --> 00:44:12,840
They can't let this sort of thing,

1112
00:44:13,720 --> 00:44:15,440
now that it's going to be public,

1113
00:44:15,440 --> 00:44:18,880
like word will get out.

1114
00:44:18,880 --> 00:44:20,440
So they will have to react.

1115
00:44:20,440 --> 00:44:22,880
Who are the easiest people to fleece?

1116
00:44:22,880 --> 00:44:26,120
The people who wouldn't notice something missing.

1117
00:44:26,120 --> 00:44:26,960
And who is that?

1118
00:44:28,080 --> 00:44:29,080
Mobility.

1119
00:44:29,080 --> 00:44:30,039
The nobles.

1120
00:44:30,039 --> 00:44:31,200
The nobles.

1121
00:44:31,200 --> 00:44:33,680
Let's see if they've been fleecing the nobles

1122
00:44:33,680 --> 00:44:36,400
for anything and then if we can get even,

1123
00:44:36,400 --> 00:44:38,320
I mean, cause whether they notice it or not,

1124
00:44:38,320 --> 00:44:39,920
they do care about their money.

1125
00:44:40,840 --> 00:44:43,360
And if he loses the nobles,

1126
00:44:43,360 --> 00:44:46,160
then that in and of itself could be,

1127
00:44:46,160 --> 00:44:48,760
you know, a good stepping stone.

1128
00:44:48,760 --> 00:44:50,120
Now, listen,

1129
00:44:51,240 --> 00:44:52,840
I don't know much,

1130
00:44:52,840 --> 00:44:54,400
but what I do know is that

1131
00:44:54,400 --> 00:44:56,640
you can't trust people with money.

1132
00:44:56,640 --> 00:44:59,680
Wait, did you mean that you can't trust people

1133
00:44:59,680 --> 00:45:00,600
as in giving them money,

1134
00:45:00,600 --> 00:45:02,039
as in I shouldn't give you money anymore,

1135
00:45:02,039 --> 00:45:02,880
or you mean people who-

1136
00:45:02,880 --> 00:45:03,720
Or the ones who already have money.

1137
00:45:03,720 --> 00:45:06,080
No, you can't keep giving me money.

1138
00:45:07,039 --> 00:45:08,719
No, that's not what I meant at all.

1139
00:45:08,719 --> 00:45:11,880
But I mean like, those guys across the river,

1140
00:45:11,880 --> 00:45:16,880
they know that there are kids like me down here.

1141
00:45:19,039 --> 00:45:21,440
And just cause you know about something

1142
00:45:21,440 --> 00:45:23,559
doesn't mean you're gonna do anything about it.

1143
00:45:23,559 --> 00:45:26,519
So I don't know if,

1144
00:45:26,519 --> 00:45:29,239
I hope Kavlaranin that you're right,

1145
00:45:29,239 --> 00:45:31,840
but how do you know that once you give this over

1146
00:45:31,840 --> 00:45:33,440
and that's all you got,

1147
00:45:33,440 --> 00:45:34,599
that they're gonna do the thing

1148
00:45:34,599 --> 00:45:36,360
you hope they're gonna do?

1149
00:45:36,360 --> 00:45:38,400
So are you saying we should

1150
00:45:38,400 --> 00:45:40,920
just make the information public?

1151
00:45:40,920 --> 00:45:41,920
Maybe?

1152
00:45:41,920 --> 00:45:43,839
And put them on blast?

1153
00:45:43,839 --> 00:45:45,360
Ooh.

1154
00:45:45,360 --> 00:45:46,799
Tell the town criers?

1155
00:45:46,799 --> 00:45:47,679
I don't know,

1156
00:45:47,679 --> 00:45:50,039
but I think that if you were to just tell

1157
00:45:50,039 --> 00:45:52,119
some rich people that other rich people

1158
00:45:52,119 --> 00:45:53,119
are being jerks,

1159
00:45:53,119 --> 00:45:54,679
they'll be like,

1160
00:45:54,679 --> 00:45:56,319
okay.

1161
00:45:56,319 --> 00:45:57,159
Okay.

1162
00:45:57,159 --> 00:45:59,799
And maybe that makes me a cynical 14 year old.

1163
00:46:00,799 --> 00:46:02,839
And maybe I'm jaded.

1164
00:46:03,840 --> 00:46:04,960
I don't think you're wrong.

1165
00:46:04,960 --> 00:46:06,920
Maybe an aggressive poster campaign

1166
00:46:06,920 --> 00:46:09,400
with some very pertinent information on it

1167
00:46:10,519 --> 00:46:12,360
would go a long way.

1168
00:46:12,360 --> 00:46:13,320
We could make posters.

1169
00:46:13,320 --> 00:46:16,559
I've got plenty of parchment back at my shop.

1170
00:46:18,000 --> 00:46:20,559
I can summon an extra set of hands

1171
00:46:20,559 --> 00:46:23,280
to help us kind of scribe things down

1172
00:46:23,280 --> 00:46:25,039
if we want to go that route.

1173
00:46:25,039 --> 00:46:28,240
That's very forward.

1174
00:46:28,240 --> 00:46:29,079
How about this?

1175
00:46:30,240 --> 00:46:31,960
Why don't we just sleep on it?

1176
00:46:32,039 --> 00:46:32,880
We've got the books.

1177
00:46:32,880 --> 00:46:34,480
Cav, maybe if you don't mind,

1178
00:46:34,480 --> 00:46:35,880
go look through them.

1179
00:46:35,880 --> 00:46:38,000
Get sort of a general sense of

1180
00:46:38,000 --> 00:46:40,440
just how bad it is.

1181
00:46:40,440 --> 00:46:43,480
And then we can meet up tomorrow morning

1182
00:46:44,400 --> 00:46:45,559
and figure out our plan.

1183
00:46:45,559 --> 00:46:47,119
To take down the government.

1184
00:46:48,000 --> 00:46:49,639
To take down the government.

1185
00:46:49,639 --> 00:46:50,960
That's right, Alydin.

1186
00:46:50,960 --> 00:46:53,400
Kavlaranne with books in hand going to review,

1187
00:46:53,400 --> 00:46:55,880
everybody going to just take the night,

1188
00:46:55,880 --> 00:46:56,720
rest,

1189
00:46:56,720 --> 00:46:59,720
and come up with a plan on the next morning.

1190
00:46:59,760 --> 00:47:02,960
Everybody goes back to their own homes.

1191
00:47:02,960 --> 00:47:05,240
We follow Bonwyn back to Everbane's

1192
00:47:05,240 --> 00:47:09,320
and you open the door and head in for the night,

1193
00:47:09,320 --> 00:47:11,080
closing and locking it behind you.

1194
00:47:11,080 --> 00:47:13,200
And there's a few things that Thane hasn't done

1195
00:47:13,200 --> 00:47:17,120
because they're your usual activities.

1196
00:47:17,120 --> 00:47:19,400
You want to walk us through that a little bit here?

1197
00:47:19,400 --> 00:47:22,400
I think that Thane probably goes around

1198
00:47:22,400 --> 00:47:25,560
and like, you know, banks all the fires and stuff,

1199
00:47:25,560 --> 00:47:29,360
but I just in an excess of caution

1200
00:47:30,000 --> 00:47:32,160
after he goes, so he doesn't know.

1201
00:47:32,160 --> 00:47:33,480
Just go and double check.

1202
00:47:33,480 --> 00:47:35,480
So I just kind of go around

1203
00:47:35,480 --> 00:47:37,280
and make sure like everything is safe.

1204
00:47:37,280 --> 00:47:40,160
Like this, I live here and there's a lot of fire.

1205
00:47:40,160 --> 00:47:42,840
So just want to be extra, extra careful.

1206
00:47:44,280 --> 00:47:46,440
Clean up, put away all the tools.

1207
00:47:46,440 --> 00:47:51,280
You know, I want a nice, easy morning when I start.

1208
00:47:51,280 --> 00:47:54,640
So I'm just kind of like futzing around, you know,

1209
00:47:54,640 --> 00:47:59,120
getting everything tidy and sorted out and yeah.

1210
00:47:59,159 --> 00:48:02,719
As you finish all these preparations

1211
00:48:02,719 --> 00:48:06,279
for what could happen,

1212
00:48:06,279 --> 00:48:08,519
you start making your way back upstairs.

1213
00:48:08,519 --> 00:48:11,480
And as you hit the top of the stairs,

1214
00:48:11,480 --> 00:48:14,480
you hear that same knocking sound

1215
00:48:14,480 --> 00:48:16,480
you heard the night before

1216
00:48:16,480 --> 00:48:19,079
coming from back down in the shop.

1217
00:48:21,119 --> 00:48:23,440
I'm going to come back down the stairs.

1218
00:48:23,440 --> 00:48:27,079
On the way, I'm going to grab something as a weapon.

1219
00:48:27,079 --> 00:48:29,079
And this is a place where we make weapons.

1220
00:48:29,079 --> 00:48:32,079
So you'd think I would grab something good,

1221
00:48:32,079 --> 00:48:32,920
but I don't.

1222
00:48:32,920 --> 00:48:34,759
Should I grab a butter knife?

1223
00:48:34,759 --> 00:48:37,519
Yeah, I just grab like whatever is the closest thing

1224
00:48:37,519 --> 00:48:39,319
as I'm like coming down the stairs.

1225
00:48:39,319 --> 00:48:41,159
She's like a cocaine-er.

1226
00:48:41,159 --> 00:48:42,440
Yeah, exactly.

1227
00:48:42,440 --> 00:48:44,239
Like something like that.

1228
00:48:44,239 --> 00:48:45,480
On it are the knife wings.

1229
00:48:45,480 --> 00:48:47,400
You take those off, cocaine only.

1230
00:48:48,840 --> 00:48:50,639
Like a broom handle or something.

1231
00:48:50,639 --> 00:48:52,880
You know, something that would just be sitting around

1232
00:48:52,880 --> 00:48:54,039
that I grab.

1233
00:48:55,319 --> 00:48:58,079
And I kind of go over cautiously

1234
00:48:58,079 --> 00:48:59,920
just to listen

1235
00:49:01,799 --> 00:49:04,799
and see, yeah, more closely what it sounds like.

1236
00:49:04,799 --> 00:49:06,279
You grab that and you come back down.

1237
00:49:06,279 --> 00:49:08,480
And as you move back down the stairs,

1238
00:49:08,480 --> 00:49:10,239
as quiet as you're trying to be,

1239
00:49:10,239 --> 00:49:14,960
the knocking stops until you get down to the bottom

1240
00:49:14,960 --> 00:49:17,799
and stop and listen.

1241
00:49:17,799 --> 00:49:22,719
And right at the spot where the desk has been pushed

1242
00:49:22,719 --> 00:49:25,960
and everything has been piled on top,

1243
00:49:25,960 --> 00:49:27,679
there's that same knocking

1244
00:49:28,279 --> 00:49:29,279
that's getting heavier.

1245
00:49:29,279 --> 00:49:31,839
She yells, not today, Satan, and goes back to bed.

1246
00:49:31,839 --> 00:49:34,519
Not today, Satan.

1247
00:49:35,559 --> 00:49:39,319
I think I feel pretty safe

1248
00:49:39,319 --> 00:49:42,639
because there's all that stuff on top of it, right?

1249
00:49:42,639 --> 00:49:44,559
So I'm not gonna start moving that stuff or anything.

1250
00:49:44,559 --> 00:49:46,319
I don't feel that safe.

1251
00:49:46,319 --> 00:49:49,000
But I could at least get a little nearer

1252
00:49:49,000 --> 00:49:52,559
and say, what do you want?

1253
00:49:52,559 --> 00:49:53,559
And feeling pretty dumb

1254
00:49:53,559 --> 00:49:56,119
because I think it's probably some kind of wild creature

1255
00:49:56,119 --> 00:49:57,279
that's not gonna answer me.

1256
00:49:58,120 --> 00:50:01,519
As you say that, the sound stops

1257
00:50:01,519 --> 00:50:06,519
and it's eerily silent in your shop.

1258
00:50:07,640 --> 00:50:09,160
And it is dark, so I'm just standing there.

1259
00:50:09,160 --> 00:50:10,400
My eyes are so wide

1260
00:50:10,400 --> 00:50:12,080
because you know when you're trying to hear in the dark

1261
00:50:12,080 --> 00:50:14,320
and for some reason you open your eyes really wide,

1262
00:50:14,320 --> 00:50:15,519
I'm like not moving.

1263
00:50:15,519 --> 00:50:20,519
You hear a long drawn out scratching sound

1264
00:50:20,519 --> 00:50:23,440
coming up from beneath the table,

1265
00:50:23,440 --> 00:50:26,960
which is followed by another bout of silence.

1266
00:50:27,639 --> 00:50:30,320
And then there's a huge thud coming up from it

1267
00:50:30,320 --> 00:50:33,519
that shakes everything on top of the table.

1268
00:50:33,519 --> 00:50:34,599
Run, bitch.

1269
00:50:37,400 --> 00:50:39,280
I feel like I'm over here watching a movie

1270
00:50:39,280 --> 00:50:41,960
being like, don't go down there.

1271
00:50:41,960 --> 00:50:42,800
Don't go in there.

1272
00:50:42,800 --> 00:50:44,199
Don't run out the stairs.

1273
00:50:44,199 --> 00:50:47,039
That's right, run out the front door.

1274
00:50:47,039 --> 00:50:49,440
Luckily I'm still dressed and everything.

1275
00:50:49,440 --> 00:50:50,880
I just went upstairs.

1276
00:50:50,880 --> 00:50:53,440
So I'm gonna stop, look at my hand

1277
00:50:53,440 --> 00:50:55,440
where I'm holding something useless,

1278
00:50:55,480 --> 00:50:58,920
throw it away, grab something that's actually a weapon

1279
00:50:58,920 --> 00:51:01,760
because again, there's like a million things laying around

1280
00:51:01,760 --> 00:51:03,200
and leave.

1281
00:51:03,200 --> 00:51:05,159
Like I'm going somewhere.

1282
00:51:05,159 --> 00:51:06,760
And honestly, I don't know if at this point

1283
00:51:06,760 --> 00:51:08,559
I even know where I'm going

1284
00:51:08,559 --> 00:51:10,880
because I know there's tunnels all around the town.

1285
00:51:10,880 --> 00:51:13,559
So I don't know where I'm gonna go to feel safe

1286
00:51:13,559 --> 00:51:15,960
because this is where I feel safe.

1287
00:51:15,960 --> 00:51:17,960
So maybe the guard house.

1288
00:51:17,960 --> 00:51:20,079
As you're looking at the broom,

1289
00:51:20,079 --> 00:51:22,440
the thudding starts up again

1290
00:51:22,480 --> 00:51:25,519
in intensity and repetitiveness.

1291
00:51:25,519 --> 00:51:27,639
As you're grabbing all these things

1292
00:51:27,639 --> 00:51:30,079
to rush out of the space and you've got a weapon

1293
00:51:30,079 --> 00:51:32,240
and you've got something to defend yourself,

1294
00:51:32,240 --> 00:51:34,559
you see that the anvil that's on top

1295
00:51:34,559 --> 00:51:37,720
is beginning to wobble from the strength of these hits

1296
00:51:37,720 --> 00:51:39,840
that are happening beneath the door.

1297
00:51:39,840 --> 00:51:42,200
We see you run out into the street

1298
00:51:42,200 --> 00:51:43,519
heading to the guard house.

1299
00:51:43,519 --> 00:51:46,880
As the door shuts, the thudding stops

1300
00:51:46,880 --> 00:51:49,720
and this anvil is rocking back and forth

1301
00:51:49,720 --> 00:51:51,599
until it tumbles to the ground.

